      "side": 1,
      "message": "The underlying problem is real: bmcweb redirects unauthenticated requests to the WebUI\u0027s /login path, and the WebUI\u0027s router doesn\u0027t know to bounce authenticated users back. \n\nThe fix should be a small addition to the router guard in src/router/index.js rather than embedding cookie checks and redirect logic inside the Login component\u0027s submit handler.\n\nIf the Redfish ?next\u003d redirect is also needed (so that after login the user is taken to the Redfish resource they originally requested), that can also be handled in the router guard or as a simple mounted() / onMounted() hook in Login.vue that checks isLoggedIn and redirects immediately -- rather than waiting for a button click.",
      "revId": "297e317a45d20ab6ddaf25a546ff373f8a279a50",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
