        "id": 1002106
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-11T16:52:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This can be dangerous.\n\nThe next query parameter value is taken from the URL and used to construct a redirect target. While the /redfish/v1 prefix check provides some protection, protocol-relative URLs like //evil.com/redfish/v1/foo could potentially bypass it depending on browser behavior with window.location.href.",
      "revId": "297e317a45d20ab6ddaf25a546ff373f8a279a50",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9e052db9_2f9e738c",
        "filename": "src/views/Login/Login.vue",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 155,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-17T10:44:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Changed startsWith(\u0027/redfish/v1\u0027) to startsWith(\u0027/redfish/v1/\u0027) trailing slash required, so that a crafted path like /redfish/v1evil is rejected. The redirect target is now window.location.origin + nextPath, ensuring it is always same-origin and the raw value is never passed to window.location.href without that origin anchor.",
      "parentUuid": "2622aa89_5de43c82",
      "revId": "297e317a45d20ab6ddaf25a546ff373f8a279a50",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
